I find that most parents are pretty accepting if they understand that a lot is going to be learned through doing that. We all need to do way more work toward that end, whether it is at home, TOPS or whatever works best.

Q: You’ve said before that many Portuguese players exit youth soccer at the U-15 age. What do you think makes a good environment for keeping players in the program?

A: Well I don’t think I can speak 100% definitively on that because the Portuguese system is still working on that. Metro, Columbus Crew, and I think SC Eastside still have permanent teams at that age. But we also know how to use those players in quite a few tournaments, creating the best environment for keeping players in the program.

It’s pretty easy to get stuck into lots of competitive events at the highest level. That is a good formula for making players awesome. It’s not sustainable over the long haul though.

We’ve definitely had kids that just hockey-poked that button in the car on the way home from a tournament and said that was it.
